  "texts": [
    "In the remaining cases, the answer was considered incorrect.",
    "At the end of the dialogue with ChatGPT and Gemini, the 7 ophthalmologists included in this research graded the quality of the answers provided by the two chatbots from 1 (poor quality) to 5 (excellent quality), according to the Global Quality Score (GQS) [25].As the main outcome of this research, we wanted to define the frequency of accurate surgical choice made by ChatGPT and Google Gemini, compared to those of glaucoma specialists facing the same clinical cases.",
    "As secondary outcome, we compared the GQS of the two chatbots.",
    "Global Quality ScoreThe GQS, introduced by Bernard et al., is a subjective rate of the overall quality of each web site [25].",
    "It consists in a 5-point Likert scale, taking into account the flow and ease of use of each web site [25]."
  ],
